   "source": [
    "# Machine Learning Classification Framework\n",
    "## Breast Cancer Diagnosis Using the Wisconsin (BRCA) Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "**Course:** ITGN 430 – Artificial Intelligence  \n",
    "**Instructor:** Dr. Mohammad Sami Zitouni  \n",
    "**Semester:** Spring 2025–2026  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Objective:** Design and implement a complete machine learning classification framework to distinguish between **Malignant (M)** and **Benign (B)** breast tumors using numerical features extracted from digitized fine needle aspirate (FNA) biopsy images.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2ee9370a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1- Introduction and Problem Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "Breast cancer is the most commonly diagnosed cancer among women worldwide, accounting for over 2.3 million new cases annually (WHO, 2022). Early and accurate detection is critical: when caught early, the 5-year survival rate exceeds 99%; in late stages, it drops below 30%.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Problem Statement:**  \n",
    "Given a set of numerical measurements derived from cell nuclei in a biopsy image, we want to train a classifier that can automatically predict whether a tumor is **Malignant (M)** or **Benign (B)**.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Component | Description |\n",
    "|-----------|-------------|\n",
    "| **Input** | 30 numerical features (mean, standard error, worst values of 10 nucleus measurements) |\n",
    "| **Output** | Binary class label: `M` (Malignant) or `B` (Benign) |\n",
    "| **Decision** | Assist pathologists in confirming/prioritizing cancer diagnoses |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why Machine Learning?**  \n",
    "Manual microscopic analysis is time-consuming, subjective, and prone to inter-observer variability. A supervised ML classifier can learn complex non-linear patterns in biopsy features and provide fast, consistent, and reproducible second opinions to support clinical decisions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "39c672a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
