    "---\n",
    "## 2 — Data Collection and Exploration\n",
    "\n",
    "### Dataset: Breast Cancer Wisconsin (Diagnostic) — BRCA\n",
    "\n",
    "| Attribute | Details |\n",
    "|-----------|--------|\n",
    "| **Source** | GitHub Repository (derived from UCI ML Repository) |\n",
    "| **Data Type** | Tabular / Numerical |\n",
    "| **Total Samples** | 569 |\n",
    "| **Features** | 30 numerical features |\n",
    "| **Classes** | 2 — Malignant (M), Benign (B) |\n",
    "| **Annotations** | Expert-labelled from pathology reports |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Feature Description:**  \n",
    "For each biopsy image, 10 nucleus properties are computed: radius, texture, perimeter, area, smoothness, compactness, concavity, concave points, symmetry, and fractal dimension. For each property, three statistics are recorded: **mean**, **standard error (SE)**, and **worst** (largest value across all nuclei in the image) — giving 30 features total."
   ]
