   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 5 — Classification Model Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "We evaluate six classifiers across different algorithmic families to identify the best model for this dataset:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Model | Family | Key Strength |\n",
    "|-------|--------|--------------|\n",
    "| Naïve Bayes | Probabilistic | Fast, good baseline for numerical features |\n",
    "| K-Nearest Neighbors | Instance-based | Non-parametric, captures local structure |\n",
    "| Decision Tree | Tree-based | Interpretable, handles non-linear boundaries |\n",
    "| SVM | Margin-based | Excellent for small, high-dimensional datasets |\n",
    "| Random Forest | Ensemble | Robust, handles correlated features, gives feature importance |\n",
    "| MLP (ANN) | Neural Network | Captures complex non-linear patterns |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Primary Choice Justification — Random Forest:**  \n",
    "Given the tabular nature of data, 30 features with known correlations, moderate dataset size (569), and binary classification with class imbalance, Random Forest is the most suitable primary model. It supports `class_weight='balanced'`, provides feature importance, and consistently achieves top performance on medical tabular datasets."
   ]
  },
