    "---\n",
    "## 6 — Training Scheme\n",
    "\n",
    "We use **Stratified 10-Fold Cross-Validation** as the primary training scheme.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why Stratified K-Fold (k=10)?**  \n",
    "- Ensures each fold preserves the original class ratio (critical given imbalance)\n",
    "- Uses all data for both training and validation (important for small datasets)\n",
    "- Produces more reliable, lower-variance performance estimates than a single train/test split\n",
    "- Widely recommended in medical AI research\n",
    "\n",
    "**Training Scheme Comparison:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Scheme | Advantage | Disadvantage |\n",
    "|--------|-----------|-------------|\n",
    "| Plain 80/20 Split | Fast | High variance, depends on single random split |\n",
    "| K-Fold CV (k=10) | Stable estimate | Does not preserve class ratio |\n",
    "| **Stratified K-Fold ** | Stable + preserves class ratio | Computationally heavier |\n",
    "| LOSO | Best for subject-level generalization | Only applies to subject-based datasets |"
   ]
  },
