    "---\n",
    "## 7 — Testing and Performance Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "### Metric Selection Justification\n",
    "\n",
    "In medical classification, **not all errors are equal**:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **False Negative (FN):** Predicting Benign when actually Malignant → *Missed cancer diagnosis — most dangerous!*\n",
    "- **False Positive (FP):** Predicting Malignant when actually Benign → Unnecessary follow-up tests — costly but not life-threatening\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, we **prioritize Recall (Sensitivity)** — minimizing FN — over Accuracy alone.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Metric | Formula | Why Important Here |\n",
    "|--------|---------|--------------------|\n",
    "| **Recall (Sensitivity)**  | TP / (TP + FN) | Minimize missed cancers |\n",
    "| Precision | TP / (TP + FP) | Minimize false alarms |\n",
    "| F1-Score | 2×P×R / (P+R) | Balance of both |\n",
    "| AUC-ROC | Area under ROC curve | Overall classifier quality |\n",
    "| Accuracy | (TP+TN) / Total | General correctness |"
   ]
  },
