   "## 8 — Deployment, Application, and Real-Life Implications\n",
   "\n",
   "The trained Random Forest model was deployed as a cloud-hosted Clinical Decision Support System using Flask, publicly accessible at 🌐 **https://workuchemeda.pythonanywhere.com/**. The practical applicability of the algorithm is demonstrated by running a deployment simulation where the values of the features of a new sample are fed into the existing StandardScaler object and then into the optimized Random Forest classifier. A class is returned, either Benign or Malignant, together with their respective probabilities, accompanied by a warning that the classifier's prediction must be used only as a helper tool for the pathologist.\n",
   "\n",
   "### Deployment Architecture\n",
   "\n",
   "| Aspect | Details |\n",
   "|--------|---------|\n",
   "| **Platform** | PythonAnywhere Cloud Server |\n",
   "| **URL** | https://workuchemeda.pythonanywhere.com/ |\n",
   "| **Backend** | Flask REST API (Python) |\n",
   "| **Input** | 30 FNA measurements via web form |\n",
   "| **Output** | Predicted class + probability scores |\n",
   "| **Speed** | < 1ms per prediction |\n",
   "| **Access** | Any device, no installation required |\n",
   "\n",
   "### Ethical Considerations\n",
   "\n",
   "- **Model is an assistant, not a replacement** — final diagnosis always rests with the pathologist\n",
   "- **Data Privacy** — patient data must comply with health data protection regulations\n",
   "- **Threshold Adjustment** — decision threshold can be lowered to further minimize False Negatives\n",
   "- **Continuous Monitoring** — model must be retrained as new clinical data accumulates\n",
   "- **Bias Concern** — model was trained on data from a single institution; may not generalize across diverse demographics"
  ]
